pr.body:
This PR addresses the bitboard organization issue by moving `CBitBoard` function bodies out of `bitboard.h` into `bitboard.cpp`, starting at `ClearLowestBit` and continuing through all subsequent methods/operators. The goal is to keep the header as interface and place implementation logic in the translation unit.

- **Header cleanup (`include/bitboard.h`)**
  - Replaced in-class definitions (from `ClearLowestBit` onward) with declarations.
  - Kept existing signatures and friend declarations intact to preserve API shape.

- **Implementation relocation (`src/bitboard.cpp`)**
  - Added out-of-class definitions for:
    - `ClearLowestBit`, `SetMask`, `ClrMask`, `CountBits`, `FindSetBit`, `FindSetBitCoord`
    - state/query helpers (`IsEmpty`, `IsNotEmpty`, `operator bool`, `operator!`)
    - bitwise/shift/arithmetic/comparison operators and compound assignments
  - Preserved logic and behavior; this is a structural move of code location.

- **Code organization impact**
  - `bitboard.cpp` is no longer a placeholder and now owns the concrete `CBitBoard` implementation body.
  - `bitboard.h` now serves as a cleaner public interface.

```cpp
// include/bitboard.h
void ClearLowestBit();
static CBitBoard SetMask(uint16_t i);
int CountBits() const;
friend CBitBoard operator&(const CBitBoard& lhs, const CBitBoard& rhs);

// src/bitboard.cpp
void CBitBoard::ClearLowestBit() { /* existing logic moved here */ }
CBitBoard CBitBoard::SetMask(uint16_t i) { /* existing logic moved here */ }
int CBitBoard::CountBits() const { /* existing logic moved here */ }
```
